msg:
Fixed salesforce.com unittest issues.
Fixed unclosed resources in unittests (eclipse compiler warnings)
Added .gitignore for JDBC test artifact files.
Replaced LGPL header with Apache2 header
Fixed charset issue caused by converting licenses.

Updated POMs with new apache.org-based groupId and apache dev
infrastructure

Improved fluent Query builder API by adding string parameter based
methods for joining
Hard rename of all 'org/eobjects' folders to 'org/apache'.

Renamed all import and package statements from 'org.eobjects' to
'org.apache'.

Added a utility ObjectInputStream for deserializing legacy
org.eobjects.metamodel objects.

Fixed usage of 'org.eobjects' namespace to 'org.apache' in xml files and
site content.

Fixed Salesforce.com UPDATE semantics error when updated ID does not
exist.
Made column super type final - it never changes.

Performance improvement to CSV reading when values are only single line
based.
Fixed ordering of value array in SingleLineCsvRow.

Upgraded version to 4.0-SNAPSHOT to avoid any version conflicts with the
eobjects.org trunk codebase

Applied patch for 'SFDC updates throw exception when no records
impacted'
Added draft module for Apache HBase.

msg: Fixed unittest coverage of new Single-Line CSV dataset.
Decreased overhead of SingleLineCsvRow by avoid the inner LazyRef.

METAMODEL-9: SalesforceDataSet is throwing exception for insert sql of
record having date/time.
fixed parent version in hbase module

METAMODEL-4: Using folder name as schema name for CSV and Fixed Width
file modules
METAMODEL-4: Added ResourceUtils for getting parent paths of resources.

METAMODEL-4: Added capability to parse column and table paths with
quoted elements in the path.

METAMODEL-4: Ensured that getParentPath(...) would return properly in
case of root file paths ("/foo" or "c:\\foo").
Upgraded Apache POI dependency to v. 3.9
METAMODEL-10: Removed 'access' module from Apache MetaModel.
Fix for bug in Salesforce DATE object formatting/parsing

Applying patch for getting rid of deprecated "_items" field in
DefaultRow
Fixed failing unittests from previous patches.
METAMODEL-26: Patch to allow custom Salesforce.com endpoint URL

Removed the specific version defined and using now the parent pom's
version.

Removing the gpg-plugin as it is defined in the parent pom under the
release profile.

Fixing licenses for 3rd party libraries, fixed the pom.xml files for
apache header.
Modified changes.txt as per comments received from group members.

Updated changes.txt in terms of formatting (no tabs or newlines) and a
few missing words.
Removed xml exclude from RAT plugin execution.

METAMODEL-29: Fixed issue with interface returned by CreateTable builder
class.
Adding the DEPENDENCIES exclude for RAT plugin.
Fixing test failures due to time differences in DateUtils seen on MacOS.
Fixing test failure on MacOS due to time difference.

Setting a fixed timestamp in the test case as with different timezones
the old way of getting time from a Date variable was failing.
METAMODEL-32: Fixed thread safety of XlsxSpreadsheetReaderDelegate

METAMODEL-33: Limited the exclusion of rat plugin. Added license headers
to integrationtest classes.

Added initial draft of DataContextFactoryBean with support for JDBC, CSV
and Excel
Added testcases for CSV datacontext factory
Added test case for Excel data contexts.

Made the DataContextFactoryBean extensible by making it possible to
specify delegate classes as the "type" parameter. This also avoids
runtime dependencies on unwanted MetaModel modules, since the factory
class no longer directly imports foreign module code.

msg: Updated CHANGES file with recent changes made to master branch
Updated and fixed typos in README file

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/hbase-module' into hbase-module

Conflicts:
	hbase/pom.xml

METAMODEL-11: Added factory delegates for MongoDB and CouchDB.
METAMODEL-11: Added parser for SimpleTableDef[], so that it is easily
externalizable in a spring property.

Extracted interface DataContextFactoryParameters to separate the
factorybean itself from the parameters given to factory delegates.
Overhauled the dependency versions a bit - upgraded to latest & greatest

METAMODEL-38: Added pooling of Connection+PreparedStatement in
JdbcCompiledQuery

METAMODEL-41: Moved SimpleTableDefParser out of sprint module and into
core.
METAMODEL-42: Applied patch for HBase GET support

Added HBase support to CHANGES.txt
Excluded a lot of transitive dependencies that are not needed for our
HBase module.
METAMODEL-44 Fixed (patch submitted via Review Board)
Converted ColumnType to an interface and made 'core' module compile/work

Adapted other modules to work with the ColumnType-as-an-interface
change.
Externalized MongoDB integration test connection information.

Improved dependency exclusion to isolate necesary and optional Hadoop
dependencies
Updated CHANGES.txt to prepare for Apache MetaModel 4.1.0 RC1 release.
Improved "starter" label link to not contain any particular issues
METAMODEL-54: Converted ColumnType from enum to interface
METAMODEL-3: Improved recognition of encodings in UnicodeWriter.
METAMODEL-56: Fixed metadata of converted JDBC LOBs.

METAMODEL-59: Added Balendra Singhs contribution (with minor
modifications).

METAMODEL-60: Adding Balendra Singh's contribution to TOP/DISTINCT ms
sql server query rewriting.

METAMODEL-45: Made abstract JDBC integration test class and implemented
it for PostgreSQL integration test.

msg: METAMODEL-18: Added a line about the improvement in changes.md
Merge branch 'METAMODEL-75' into master. It fixes #4.

METAMODEL-84: Use ElasticSearch document ID as primary key and enable
optimized PK lookup queries.
METAMODEL-88: For the ElasticSearch module find a better way than sleep to ensure data is in sync.
METAMODEL-90 - Csv and Excel Data Context constructors accept non existing files. Added javadoc
Fixed unittest failure when no cassandra port specified
METAMODEL-85: Fixed null-filtering bug in JDBC update and delete
Updated CHANGES.md with all relevant issues for the 4.3.0 release
Updated parent-pom and specified git scm provider for release
Updated website and mailing list links throughout pom.xml and MDs
Updated all <version> tags to not have "-incubating" suffix
Removed incubator DISCLAIMER. Fixed unittest relying on incubator URL.
Added additional categories to DOAP file
Upgrade of dependencies slf4j and Google Guava
METAMODEL-78: Fixed SELECT DISTINCT queries that returned duplicates
Updated CHANGES.md with info on METAMODEL-78
METAMODEL-106: Added error handling/logging when index/docType not found

METAMODEL-109: CassandraDataContext throws IllegalArgumentException with
proper message instead of NPE when keystore does not exist.
METAMODEL-79: Added support for Insert, Create and Drop table

Refactored QueryPostprocessDataContext to easy "simple where" query
optimization by subclasses
Fixed filtering and paging order in post processing scenario

Added support for DELETE and thereby also simplified UPDATE statements
on ElasticSearch. Fixes METAMODEL-79.

METAMODEL-115: Fixes query parser to allow lower-case function names
etc.
This fixes #7
METAMODEL-79: Fixed issues raised by Dennis Du Krger on review board.
Fixed version name in CHANGES.md before release
Removed .isCreated() call which is not available in JDK6 version of ES

Improved query parser's tolerance for lowercase WHERE clause delims.
Fixes #10
METAMODEL-123: Added Dennis Du Krger's fix.

[METAMODEL-93] - Added compatibility with HBase version 1.0.0
Fixes #12
Added support for multiple comma-separated items in Query.select(String)

METAMODEL-128: Fixed bug in DataSet ordering with aggregation function
Fixes #13

Updated the return-type of createElasticSearchDataContext(...)
Fixes #15
Allow empty spaces before AS keyword.  This closes #METAMODEL-138
Update CHANGES.MD with METAMODEL-138 fix. Fixes #22
Modify WIP tag to match the release version
METAMODEL-148: Updated module structure to have a base hadoop module
METAMODEL-148: Updated HBase version and added dependency exclusions
METAMODEL-148: Updated as per review remarks
Fixed current build issues with missing license headers & banned deps
Added a proper integration test for the HdfsResource

Made HdfsResource non-closeable to avoid statefulness.

Integration test shows very similar performance metrics.
Further improved the HdfsResource by managing filesystem.close() better

METAMODEL-160: Added support for Apache Hive
Fixes #31

Adding hadoop and hbase modules to the MetaModel-full artifact.

Also sorting the dependencies alphabetically to find out easier what is
missing in the future.
Removing the dot in the mvn clean install command in the README

Adds ability to read folders from FileResource and HdfsResource

This will allow FileResource and HdfsResource to use a folder as a complete resource. It will skip any subfolder and only use files in the folder. Before opening files, they will be sorted them alphabetically by name (actually it uses the natural ordering of the File/FileStatus object, but that is the pathname/url sorted alphabetically).

Use JUnit 4 TemporaryFolder rule for temp folder.

This removes the Java 7 dependency in the FileResourceTest by using
JUnit 4's TemporaryFolder rule. This also ensures that the folder
will always be deleted after running the test.

The license header in AbstractDirectoryInputStream has also been put
where it is supposed to be, and minor cleanups of imports and code
style has been done.
Updated CHANGES.md with latest issues fixed.

METAMODEL-164: Fixed and refactored ES mapping parser to use real map.

Previously the parser was (by accident I think) using the toString()
representation of that same map which made it very vulnerable towards
parsing issues.
METAMODEL-170: Removed any Java 6 specifics from build files
METAMODEL-170: Removed hack to avoid invalid test under ES version 0.x

METAMODEL-173: Added Resource.append() and Resource.write() methods

implemented an abstract Resource class for reuse of common functionality

METAMODEL-173: Changed CsvUpdateCallback to use Resource.write() 
or Resource.append() when necesary.

METAMODEL-176: Fixed

Also added DataSet.close() to a few places where it was giving log
warnings during build/test

msg: Using version 4.6.0 since new features (DynamoDB) was added.

Deprecated Ref, Func and Predicate in favor of java.util.function

"Ref" to be replaced by Supplier.
"Func" to be replaced by Function.
"Predicate" to be replaced by Predicate.
"Action" to extend Consumer (allowing for throwing checked exceptions).
"UncheckedFunc to extend Function.

Also added `@SuppressWarning` on method that the Java 8 compiler is
emitting warnings for while the code being alright.
Removed strange comment-line as pointed out by Tomasz G.
Removed Java 7 build from Travis CI config

msg:
Refactoring.
Column type MAP was removed and ARRAY was replaced by LIST.
Refactored HBaseRowInsertionBuilder, so it uses the _columns of the AbstractRowBuilder instead of its own, to make sure the model stays consistent.
Removed table exists check. Let's assume the createTable message throws an exception when it fails to create the table.

Refactoring:
* Removal of ColumnTypeResolver._columnTypes field.
* String constants in Neo4jDataContext.
* JSONArray => List<String> conversion in Neo4jDataSet.
Refactoring: New Neo4jDataContext.NEO4J_* constants are not public anymore (package private).
HBase Improvements - did some refactoring, added comments, added unittest
HBase unittests improvements (fixed issues when the testfile wasn't setup)

- Where missing added final qualifiers to method parameters.
- Moved static methods around to more logic locations. From my point of view the HBaseColumn class is not a Helper class to provide those.
- Changed the signature of the HBaseRowInsertionBuilder constructor, so it take a List of HBaseColumn object as a parameter, this makes it possible to remove a few of the Helper methods which cast List<HBaseColumn> to List<Column> and vice versa.
- Refactored the logic which looks up the id column in an array or list.
- Removed the "public" getHBaseColumnsInternal() method from HBaseTable, which essentially was only invoked in combination with a static getColumnFamilies method. Instead I added a getColumnFamilies() method to the HBaseTable class which return the column families for that HBase table.

Merge pull request #3 from GerardDellemann/feature/hbase-improvements-refactoring

Refactoring code and implementing feedback
HBase improvements (when creating a HBase table, the ID-column is not a required parameter, because that's always created).

Refactored test so they no longer extends TestCase (and as such are no longer JUnit 3, but JUnit 4 tests) and they use "assumeTrue" to check if they should run or not. This reduces a lot of boiler plate code, because now we don't need to call the "isConfigured" method in each test method.

Also added some extra null check in the code which cleans up after test, because some nullpointer exceptions were thrown when the tests were skipped.

Merge pull request #4 from GerardDellemann/feature/hbase-improvements-assume-in-tests

Refactored to remove boiler plate isConfigured checks
HBase improvements - Refactoring (mostly small improvements, the getHBaseClient method has been moved to HBaseDataContent)
Added InterfaceStability class with stability annotations.
Removed referenced to Object.finalize() (deprecated since JDK 9)
Removed duplicate and standardized reference to junit.

HBaseClient.java:
- Remove overabundant `;` on line 111 ("try (final Table table = _connection.getTable(TableName.valueOf(tableName));) {").
- Remove overabundant " == true" on line 112 ("if (rowExists(table, rowKeyAsByteArray) == true) {").
- On line 115 use a Marker object when inserting variables into log messages.
- Add final modifier on line 144 ("public void createTable(String tableName, Set<String> columnFamilies) {").

HBaseCreateTableBuilder.java:
- On line 81 make the parameters of the setColumnFamilies method final.
HBaseRow.java:
- Revert remmoval of empty line (62).
HBaseRowDeletionBuilder.java:
- The _dataContext field member has to be made final
- On line 58 make the key par

- Reverted newly introduced constructor for AbstractRowInsertionBuilder.
- Refactored HBaseUpdateCallback so it more strictly adheres to the MetaModel UpdateCallback interface. It is no longer public.
- Removed some of the overabundant constructors for HBaseColumn and changed the ID column's column type to ColumnType.BINARY.
- Refactored the HBaseRowInsertionBuilder, so it can be instantiated without the columns for the update. Move all possible "value" methods there, because it can't determine based on the Table which columns are available for updating (because Big Table doesn't work in that manner), you can use the "value" method to dynamically add HBase columns for inserting.
- Updated unit tests accordingly.

- Made HBaseColumn private, even though in the future, I would like to see something like a WideColumn interface to use for Wide Column stores.
- Refactored the HBaseCreateTableBuilder so you don't have to pass the column families to the constructor, but it can determine them based on the columns set on it using the "withColumn" method.
- Refactored the HBaseDeletionBuilder so it uses the "whereItems" instead of the custom "setKey" method to determine what rows it deletes.
- Refactored the HBaseRowInsertionBuilder so it works with "normal" MetaModel columns and it will construct HBaseColumn for internal usage only.
- Removed the no longer needed, not part of the interface createTable method from HBaseUpdateCallback
- Move some test cases to a new HBaseClientTest class, because they specifically test the HBaseClient class
- Updated some test in accordance with the refactorings mentioned above.
Reverted back to private as it was before.
Overriding setUp method with @Before annotation to make sure setUp method on parent class is invoked before running tests.
Throw IllegalArgumentException when trying to delete a row with an empty row key.

- Refactored contructing String representation of byte arrays.
- Have the HBaseRowInsertionBuilder no longer extend the AbstractRowInsertionBuilder, because it does things structurally different in some parts.
HBase Improvement - Fixed a bug for inserting NULL values and refactored some tests
HBase improvements - Small refactoring on loging
Made builders package private and added @InterfaceStability.Evolving annotation to HBaseDataContext class.
add support for Oracle "TIMESTAMP WITH (LOCAL_)TIME_ZONE" column type.
Fixes: Big integer's last some digits become zero after read.
Follow Coding guidelines, replace Tabs with spaces.
Don't support primary keys with Hive

Added integration tests that prove MetaModel doesn't handle nested data in Elasticsearch in a correct manner.
Pushed changes to better indicate the problem.
Fixed resolution of type of nested objects for Elasticsearch.

Created a unit test, that MetaModel is unable to work with a document indexed by Elasticsearch which contains dots in its fieldnames. Note that this is actually caused by Elasticsearch, because the mapping returned for such a document by Elasticsearch doesn't match the source returned by Elasticsearch when getting the source of a search hit. (see https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-hadoop/issues/853 and related issues for more info on this).

Introduced a workaround for the fact that Elasticsearch returns data based on indexed documents with dots in the field names in an inconsistent manner. I.e the mapping it returns for such documents indicate those kind of fields are treated as nested objects. But if you get the source map of such a document from Elasticsearch, it still contains the original fieldnames (with dots in them).
